Weekly Progress Report


Name: Mantasha Anish Shaikh
Course: BCA – AI & Data Analytics
Domain: Predictive Maintenance
Date of Submission: April 2026

Week Ending: 02

I. Overview

This week focused on developing and analyzing multiple predictive maintenance projects aimed at estimating equipment failures using machine learning techniques. The work involved handling real-world industrial datasets, including turbofan engines, bearings, and gearbox systems. Additionally, efforts were made to strengthen practical knowledge in time-series analysis and predictive modeling.

II. Achievements

1. Project Development & Implementation
Successfully worked on multiple predictive maintenance projects using real-world datasets.
Applied machine learning techniques to analyze equipment health and predict failures.
Built models for Remaining Useful Life (RUL) prediction and fault detection.

2. Project Contributions
Project 6: Turbofan Engine RUL Prediction
Developed a model to predict Remaining Useful Life using multivariate time-series sensor data.
Worked with datasets containing multiple engine cycles and degradation patterns.
Understood operational variability and sensor noise handling.
Dataset Highlights:
26 features including operational settings and sensor readings
Multiple dataset variants (FD001–FD004) with different conditions and faults
Project 7: Bearing Life Prediction
Analyzed vibration signal data collected from bearing systems.
Worked with high-frequency time-series data (20 kHz sampling rate).
Identified fault patterns such as inner race, outer race, and roller defects.
Project 8: Gearbox Fault Prediction
Implemented fault classification models using vibration sensor data.
Studied gearbox behavior under different load conditions.
Classified machine conditions into healthy and faulty states.

3. Learning & Skill Development
Gained hands-on experience with:
Python programming
Data analysis using Pandas and NumPy
Machine learning using Scikit-learn
Data visualization using Matplotlib and Seaborn
Improved understanding of time-series data processing and predictive modeling techniques.

